# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# LiteLLM Proxy — Secrets for free-tier models
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# No API keys are required — all models are free tier.
# If you want higher rate limits, set keys for individual providers.
#
# ⚠️  RECOMMENDATION: Set secrets as machine environment variables instead of
#     keeping them in files. Export in your shell profile (~/.bashrc, ~/.zshrc):
#
#       export LITELLM_MASTER_KEY="sk-codefreedom-local"
#       export OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY_MNP="your-key"   # optional, for higher limits
#       export NVIDIA_API_KEY="your-key"              # optional, for higher limits
#       export OPENROUTER_API_KEY="your-key"          # optional, for higher limits
#
#     This keeps sensitive values out of version control and config files.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── LiteLLM Proxy Master Key ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used to authenticate requests to the local proxy.
# This is the ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN value used in Claude Code profiles.
# LITELLM_MASTER_KEY=sk-codefreedom-local   # 👈 set via: export LITELLM_MASTER_KEY="sk-codefreedom-local"

# ── Optional API keys (for higher rate limits) ─────────────────────────────
# Leave empty to use free tier without auth. Set as machine env vars instead.
# OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY_MNP=
# NVIDIA_API_KEY=
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
